IN	Nonstick vegetable oil spray
IN	1 unpeeled large eggplant (1 1/2 to 1 3/4 pounds), cut into 1/2-inch cubes
IN	2 medium yellow bell peppers, cut into 1/2-inch squares
IN	2 cups grape tomatoes
IN	3 large garlic cloves, divided
IN	1/3 cup olive oil
IN	2 cups (firmly packed) fresh basil leaves, divided
IN	1 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese, divided
IN	1/4 cup pine nuts
IN	1 28-ounce can whole tomatoes in juice
IN	1 cup heavy whipping cream
IN	1 pound rigatoni
IN	1 pound whole-milk mozzarella cheese, cut into 1/2-inch cubes
PR	Preheat oven to 425Â°F. Spray large rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray; add eggplant and peppers. Cut tomatoes in half lengthwise; add to sheet. Using garlic press, squeeze 1 garlic clove onto vegetables. Drizzle vegetables with oil; toss. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast vegetables until tender, stirring often, 35 to 45 minutes.
PR	Combine 2/3 cup basil, 1/2 cup Parmesan, pine nuts, and 1 garlic clove in mini processor. Blend until crumbly. Season topping with salt.
PR	Blend tomatoes with juice, cream, 1 1/3 cups basil, and 1 garlic clove in processor until smooth. Season sauce with salt and pepper.
PR	Cook pasta in pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally; drain. Return to pot. Toss with vegetables, sauce, and 1/2 cup Parmesan. Transfer to 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with mozzarella and pine nut topping.
PR	Bake pasta until heated through, 25 to 35 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes and serve.
